  "text": "Sex differences in expression were examined using OE, both across genotypes and for each homozygous X sub genotype separately. A majority of genes (84%) showed a significant effect of sex in the overall test. The distribution of sex effects is shown in figure S3 , Supplementary Material online. Femalebiased expression was more common than male-biased expression (5,380 vs. 3,444 genes, respectively), consistent with previous studies [CITATION_1] however, see Zhang et al. 2007 ). There was no evidence for genetic variation for sex bias (supplementary table S6, Supplementary Material online).",
